    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="872"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12834.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>124. I have just returned from the Constitutionalist camp where, in the presence
                    of Robles Dominguez and also Silliman, I held a long conference with Carranza
                    who notwithstanding my most arduous efforts and tenacious arguments did not even
                    accept the idea of any arrangement with Carbajal to save the situation which is
                    really pressing. I have been happy enough to find at least a formula accepted by
                    Carranza for the peaceful occupation of the capital, which I will communicate to
                    you as soon as all details are completed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
